The syllabus includes the main theories of educational innovation and change management on the group and organizational levels. During the course the students will compile a practical "toolkit" that will help them draw together the basic know-how of change management and innovation in an educational organization.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The student is knowledgeable about general future trends in the field of education and, based on these trends, can plan educational innovations that support student learning and develop future skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Having passed the course the student will: •	Describe global trends in the field of education; •	Compare various cases of educational innovative changes based on different models of change management; •	Plan educational innovations in an educational institution based on evidence-based practices; •	Demonstrate an increased readiness for change; •	Show improved collaboration skills.
